dct_title_s: Essexiae descriptio: The description of Essex; Amstelodami, sumptibus Ioannis Ianssonii.
dct_description_sm: Relief shown pictorially. Title cartouche in lower right corner is surrounded by an angel with a lyre, a cherub, and Pan with his pipes. There are ships in the ocean. This state was published in atlases by Jan Jansson in 1636 and 1637. From the Jansson Appendix Atlas 1636-1680, title created to represent a unique collection within the Clark Library, University of Michigan. 1 map; 37 x 47 cm.
dct_rights_sm: This map is in the public domain.
